Romania, 21 March:
The Ministry of Internal Affairs recommends that "[...] between 6.00h - 22.00h, the movement of persons outside the home/household is [...] to
be done only for the following reasons:
a) for professional purposes, including from home/household to the location/locations where the professional activity takes place and back;
b) for purchasing goods that cover the basic needs of persons and pets/domestic animals, as well as goods needed for professional activity;
c) for medical assistance which cannot be postponed or performed remotely;
d) for justified reasons, such as to ensure child care/attendance, attendance or assistance to elderly, sick or disabled persons, or the death of a family member;
e) short exits nearby home/household, for individual physical activity of persons and for the needs of pets/domestic animals."
The policy has no explicit end date.

On December 17, 2020, Romania announced that "official ceremonies, organized by public authorities and institutions in closed spaces, as well as working meetings such as, but not limited to, parliamentary sessions, sittings, preparatory working meetings / meetings of the Government / commissions, may be carried out in compliance with the following health protection measures:

a) wearing a protective mask, so as to cover the nose and mouth, by all participants;
b) mandatory hand disinfection, for all participants;
c) maintaining the physical distance of at least 1 meter between the participants and ensuring an area of ​​at least 4 sqm / person;
d) ventilating the rooms for a period of at least 10 minutes at a time interval of at most 2 hours;
e) application of collective and individual hygiene rules to prevent contamination and limit the spread of SARS-CoV-2 virus."

On December 17, 2020, Romania announced that "the activities organized in open spaces, on the occasion of the commemoration of the heroes of the Romanian Revolution of December 1989, are allowed with the participation of at most 100 people and the observance of the following sanitary protection measures:

a) wearing a protective mask, so as to cover the nose and mouth, by all participants;
b) the obligatory disinfection of the hands, for all the persons who arrive in the space where the activity takes place;
c) maintaining the physical distance of at least 1 meter between the participants and ensuring an area of ​​at least 4 sqm / person;
d) disinfection of the hands of the persons who distribute any materials during the activity;
e) application of collective and individual hygiene rules to prevent contamination and limit the spread of SARS-CoV-2 virus."

